      },
      "date": "2014-03-07 22:38:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(4 comments)\n\nThis isn't really enough since the FIFO is opened O_NONBLOCK. Using fprintf() can issue small writes the first of which may succeed. It would be better to ensure a single write() to the FIFO:\n\n \nchar buf[PIPE_BUF];\n \nFILE *file = fmemopen(buf, sizeof(buf), \"w\");\nrc = llapi_json_write_list(event, file);\nif (rc < 0)\n        /* Bail. */;\n \nfclose(file);\n \nwrite(fd, buf, strlen(buf));",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
